history.content:
I cannot speak for EE classes but CS 186 often expands to accept as much of the wait list as possible.

For both CS 186 and 188, we have capped enrollment right now to 70% of the total enrollment until we know how TA hiring goes. It's better to be cautious than to enroll more students than can be supported by teaching staff.

Hi! I am a junior transfer and will declare CS after this semester(waiting for the grades of CS61B and CS70). So far, I have been placed on waitlists for EE16B, CS170, and CS 188. What are my chances of getting into these classes? Any suggestions?
